text: The 1996 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship Final was the 65th All- Ireland Final and the deciding match of the 1996 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship. It is an inter-county camogie tournament for the top teams in Ireland. Cork led 1-9 to 1-6 at half-time. After that they went on to regret missed chances.
